{"sectionId":759,"sectionIdLiteral":"759","humanId":"lesson-336","volumeId":"workbook","locale":"en","titleInfo":{"title":"Forgiveness lets me know that minds are joined.","ownlineNumber":"Lesson 336"},"annotation":"W-336","bodyHtml":"<div class=\"acim-text lesson-336\"> <div data-paragraph-id=\"759#1\"><p class=\"p-normal\"><span class=\"pnr\">1.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#1:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>Forgiveness is the means appointed for perception‚Äôs ending.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#1:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Knowledge is restored after perception first is changed, and then gives way entirely to what remains forever past its highest reach.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#1:3\"><span class=\"snr\">3</span>For sights and sounds, at best, can serve but to recall the memory that lies beyond them all.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#1:4\"><span class=\"snr\">4</span>Forgiveness sweeps away distortions, and opens the hidden altar to the truth.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#1:5\"><span class=\"snr\">5</span>Its lilies shine into the mind, and call it to return and look within, to find what it has vainly sought without.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#1:6\"><span class=\"snr\">6</span>For here, and only here, is peace of mind restored, for this the dwelling place of God Himself.</span></p></div> <div data-paragraph-id=\"759#2\"><p class=\"p-italic\"><span class=\"pnr\">2.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#2:1\"><span class=\"snr noprint\">1</span>In quiet may forgiveness wipe away my dreams of separation and of sin.</span> <span data-sentence-id=\"759#2:2\"><span class=\"snr\">2</span>Then let me, Father, look within, and find Your promise of my sinlessness is kept; Your Word remains unchanged within my mind, Your Love is still abiding in my heart.</span></p></div> </div>","firstWords":"Forgiveness is the means appointed for perception‚Äôs ending. Knowledge is restored after perception first is changed, and th